Plural of index is indices and I would add a "the" before "Fibonacci". The statement needs a bit of a rework imo, something like "given a list of indices, output the fibonacci numbers with those indices".  Same with output, something like "<<N lines:>> The fibonacci number with the [[N]]-th index" should work just fine.
Otherwise this is fine, works well for reverse with the given testcases, my only gripe would be the odd input-output format (one line in, multiple lines out), but that's ok
With numbers > 2^63, this becomes "write a program to handle really big numbers" instead of the fairly easy original puzzle.
Right, I didn't think about it, I will change it.
You don't need the "in this contribution" part
